* North of Coquihalla Hwy;* Access via Kingsvale Bridge (approx 50m upstream);* Parking area located on downstream side of bridge off gravel road;* Kick area upstream of bridge;* Width and Depth measurements taken downstream of kick area;* Water chemistry taken at 11:30 am PDT;* No. benthic invertebrate sample jars = 3; sample taken from riffle; typical depth in kick area = 30 cm

* Access via Bulgur Rd before reserve; park by boat launch area near Bulgur Rd;* Approx 15 km downstream of town of Hope;* Limited access across stream (other side from boat launch and Bulgur Rd); can hike in here by fishermen  *Car left in gravel parking area (by Bulgur Rd)approximately 400m from sampling site;* Kick area upstream of boat launch on Bulgur Rd sde of river;* Width and Depth measurements taken downstream of kick area;* Caution as murky/silty water - hard to see footing; slippery rocks; drops off quickly - recommend testing depth with pole (kicknet) before stepping out);* Water chemistry taken at 10:00 am PDT ;* Benthic Invert sample taken in straight run; 1 benthic invertebrate sample jar;* Typical depth in kick area = 45 cm

* At Elk Falls Provincial Park;* Upstream of confluence with Campbell River;* Access from Campsite #2;* Kick area upstream of Hwy crossing;* Caution: fast and deep thalweg;* Did not kick all the way across as too deep and fast on right bank (as viewed looking downstream);* Water chemistry measurements conducted at 15:00 PDT;* 1 benthic invertebrate sample jar;* Typical depth in kick area = 30 cm;* Riffle sampled

Site is North of the Coquihalla Highway, access is via a gravel road over the Kinsvale Bridge.  Kick area is upstream from the bridge, forest on both sides of the river upstream from the bridge.  Pasture land downstream.

Access via Bulgur Road before reserve; downstream approximately 15km from the town of Hope.  Good Riparian zone on either side of river, field pasture behind riparian zone on S side. Difficult access on N side (hike in by fishermen). Boat launch downstream of kick area.

Site is in Elk Falls Provincial Park, upstream of a highway and upstream of the confluence with the Campbell River.  Access is via campsite #2.  Campsites on N side of river, good riparian zone next to S side of river with residential behind it.  The S side of the river is very fast and deep near the bank so it was not possible to kick all the way across.
